== Sweet Potato ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Dressing and Gochujang Mayo ==

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons
down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @rice vinegar{30%ml}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{},
then set your dressing aside.

In a small bowl, mix together the @gochujang paste{30%g} (use less if you'd
prefer things milder) and @mayonnaise{64%g}. Set aside.

== Gyozas ==

When the potatoes have about 10 mins left, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a
large #frying pan{} on low heat.

Once hot, add the @chicken gyozas{1%pack} and fry until golden, ~{3%minutes}.

Add @water{4%tbsp} to the pan and cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}). Cook until
piping hot, ~{3%minutes} more. Remove from the heat.

Add half the @sweet chilli sauce{48%g} to the pan and turn to glaze the gyozas
in the sauce.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

When everything's ready, add the roasted sweet potatoes, carrot ribbons and
baby gem to the bowl of dressing and toss to coat.

Share the salad between your serving #bowls{}. Drizzle over the gochujang mayo
and top with the glazed gyoza.

Spoon over the remaining sweet chilli sauce and finish by sprinkling over the
peanuts.

Enjoy!